    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1966-12-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1966-12-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="159"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d159">
                <head>159. Memorandum From President <persName corresp="#p_JLB1" type="from"
                        >Johnson</persName> to His Armed Forces Aide (<persName type="to"
                        >Cross</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d159fn1">Source:
                        Washington National Records Center, <gloss target="#t_OSD1">OSD</gloss>
                        Files: <gloss target="#t_FRC1">FRC</gloss> 330 70 A 4443, 384 Civil Defense
                        (Aug-) 1966. No classification marking.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1966-12-21">December 21, 1966</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Under my responsibility to activate the Emergency Broadcast System, I direct that
                    in the event the Commander in Chief, North American Air Defense Command,
                    declares Air Defense Emergency Red condition, the White House Communications
                    Agency shall be authorized to activate the Emergency Broadcast System and the
                    Office of Civil Defense shall be authorized to follow with the dissemination of
                    appropriate warning messages.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JLB1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Lyndon B. Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
